channel.title: Need JDK 5.0 or 6.0
channel.description:
Where can I get JDK 6.0 or JDK 5.0?
I need it to compile my server. If anyone has the link could you please post for me, it will be very helpful.
Thanks.

item.title: Need JDK 5.0 or 6.0
item.dc:creator: @TeleNubby TeleNubby
item.description:
@TeleNubby wrote:

[quote=“xxdanxx135, post:2, topic:153647”]https://sdlc3e.sun.com/ECom/EComActionServlet/DownloadPage:~:com.sun.sunit.sdlc.content.DownloadPageInfo;jsessionid=12B4CFEF2B8383F90830E681BA61ABD6;jsessionid=12B4CFEF2B8383F90830E681BA61ABD6

And make sure to use the online version

~dan[/quote]
Download the latest JDK by typing “JDK” in the Google search box and then hit “I’m feeling lucky.”

After that, change the path in your batch file that runs the javac compiler to jdk1.6.0_03 instead of what there is currently there.
